@glenn-jocher Indeed. The problem was that we thought the trained weights are outputted to the same file they were inputted in the call to train (yolov3.pt), but they are not - they are outputed to the (originally only containing a script to download the pretrained weights) "weights" directory (and only at the end of each epoch, I think?).
Now that we are actually using the correct learned weights (ie best.pt), we see that indeed the network is only aware of the classes in our dataset.
Thanks again for the quick and kind replies!

@YanivO1123 yes all training results are logged to a single directory which is reported to you after training completes. Please see the Train Custom Data Tutorial for details:
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Train-Custom-Data

